loadBalancerLogic.description:
This field allows you to enter <a href="/cdn/docs/edge-logic/intro">Edge Logic</a> to customize load balancing. A subset of the <a href="/cdn/docs/edge-logic/supported-directives"> directives</a> can be used. Refer to the basic directives listed in the <i>baseLbDirectives</i> field of the response to the <a href="#operation/get-cdn-systemConfigs">system configuration API</a>. Currently, these include "if", "else", "elseif", "set", "return", "add_header", "deny", "allow", "access_log_sampling", and "proxy_set_header." In addition, some advanced Edge Logic directives, identified by the system configuration API's <i>advancedLbDirectives</i>, can be enabled for your account if needed. Please contact our support team if you require any of them. <br/> Example use: <br /><code>
if ($http_user_agent = bot) { return 403;}
</code>

